Now that we've found the amplitudes A and B, let's substitute them back into the expression for the wave function:
\begin{align*}
|\psi(t)&=(1/2)e^{-i\omega t}|+\rangle+(1/2)e^{i\omega t}|-\rangle\\
&=(1/2)[cos(\omega t)-isin(\omega t)]|+\rangle+i(1/2)[sin(\omega t)+icos(\omega t)]|- \rangle
\end{align*}
But recall that $\omega=0$ therefore
\begin{align*}
