## Step 7: Expressing Expectation Values in Terms of Trigonometric Functions
Note that all the expectation values contain expressions like $(|+-\rangle+|--\rangle-(|++\rangle+|--)$. Recall that
\begin{align*}
|+-\rangle&=|+\rangle\otimes|-\rangle\\
|--\rangle&=|-\rangle\otimes|-\rangle\\
|++\rangle&=|+\rangle\otimes|+\rangle\\
|--\rangle&=|-\rangle\otimes|-\rangle
\end{align*}
Therefore, if we define
\begin{align*}
U=e^{-i\pi/4}\equiv cos(\pi/4)-isnin(\pi/4),
\end{align*}
then
\begin{align*}
|+-\rangle&=U|00\rangle\\
|--\rangle&=V|11\rangle\\
|++\rangle&=W|01\rangle\\
|--\rangle&=X|10\rangle
\end{align*}
Thus, we may express the previous result as
\begin{align*}
<-s_x>&=-(1/2)Re(U^\dag W-U^\dag X)\\
